While abortion presents a major dividing mark in the Christian faith, Christians should still find agreeable matter in their perspectives on women’s rights and dignity. Christians of all ethnicities and locations within Cambodia must demand respect for the unborn. In order to attain these goals, Cambodians must look to the Bible for its authoritative and life-giving quality regarding the beings’ right to life.
